## Lessons Learned (from prior sessions)

1. **`optimizer=auto` overrides lr0 to 0.002** — ALWAYS use OPTIMIZER="AdamW" explicitly to control LR
2. **Fine-tuning from best.pt often fails on nano models** — the warmup phase disrupts learned features; prefer training from pretrained weights
3. **Resolution (IMGSZ) is the #1 lever** for high-res source images — try IMGSZ=1024 early
4. **Short training (100 epochs) can beat long training (2000 epochs)** for nano models — don't assume longer is better
5. **Small validation sets (<200 images) cause high metric variance** — single-epoch metrics may be partly luck
6. **LR schedule depends on epoch count** — lrf=0.002 with 2000 epochs decays too slowly; link lrf recommendation to EPOCHS setting

---

## Parameter Bounds (Safety Rails)

Never set parameters outside these ranges:

| Parameter | Min | Max | Notes |
|-----------|-----|-----|-------|
| LR | 0.0001 | 0.05 | Outside → divergence or stall |
| LR_FINAL | 0.0001 | 0.05 | Usually same as LR |
| EPOCHS | 50 | 500 | 50–300 typical; >500 hits diminishing returns on small datasets |
| BATCH | -1 (auto) or 2 | 64 | Auto (-1) recommended |
| IMGSZ | 640 | 1280 | Must be multiple of 32 |
| PATIENCE | 20 | 100 | 20–100; >100 rarely improves results on small datasets |
| DEGREES | 0.0 | 45.0 | >45 rarely helps |
| MOSAIC | 0.0 | 1.0 | 0 disables, 1.0 always on |
| WEIGHT_DECAY | 0.0 | 0.005 | >0.005 too aggressive |

---

## Golden Rules

1. **Change ONE thing per cycle** — if you change LR AND model AND epochs, you can't attribute improvement
2. **Always use best.pt from previous run** when fine-tuning (Action F); pretrained weights when swapping arch (Action C)
3. **Always write next_instruction.md** before exiting — your next self has NO other memory
4. **Check if training is already running** before launching — NEVER run two jobs simultaneously
5. **Monitor overfitting gap** — with limited images, overfitting is the main risk
6. **Respect STOP conditions** — don't waste GPU cycles on a broken setup
7. **Record EVERYTHING** — future you needs exact numbers to make good decisions
8. **Try IMGSZ=1024 at least once** if original images are high-res
9. **Don't be afraid to switch datasets** — if primary is noisy, fallback may be better
10. **Use OPTIMIZER="AdamW" explicitly** — never use "auto" (it overrides your LR settings)
